for Poisson noise in our stochastic background explicitly â€“ as its
contribution is small. For each candidate, we simulated 10,000 fake
periodograms using a plc model to describe the broad band noise,
with parameters drawn at random from the mapped M-dimensional
parameter space described above. This approach accounts for the
intrinsic uncertainty in our estimated broad-band noise and there-
fore provides a more conservative significance estimate for a QPO
candidate. We treated each simulated dataset in an identical man-
ner to the real data, first by fitting each fake periodogram using
